zetui
=====

ANSI/C89 terminal UI library, single-header, STB-style.
First-class Zig bindings. Built with zig build.


REQUIREMENTS
------------

  - POSIX.1-2008 compatible OS (Linux, macOS, BSDs)
  - C89 compiler (gcc, clang)
  - Zig >= 0.16.0 (build system and optional bindings)


INSTALLATION
------------

Drop include/zetui.h into your project. In exactly one translation unit:

    #define ZETUI_IMPLEMENTATION
    #include "zetui.h"

All other TUs just include the header.

To build as a static library via zig:

    zig build
    # produces zig-out/lib/libzetui.a and zig-out/include/zetui.h


USAGE — C
---------

    zetui_ctx_t *ctx = zetui_init();
    if (!ctx) return 1;

    zetui_cursor_hide(ctx);
    while (running) {
        zetui_clear(ctx);
        zetui_draw_str(ctx, 1, 1, "hello", zetui_style_default());
        zetui_present(ctx);

        zetui_event_t ev = zetui_wait_event(ctx, -1);
        if (ev.type == ZETUI_EVENT_KEY &&
            ev.data.key.ch == 'q') running = 0;
    }
    zetui_shutdown(ctx);

See examples/hello.c and examples/demo.c.


USAGE — ZIG
-----------

In build.zig add the module exposed by this repo, then:

    const zetui = @import("zetui");

    var tui = try zetui.Context.init();
    defer tui.deinit();

    tui.cursorHide();
    while (running) {
        tui.clear();
        tui.drawStr(1, 1, "hello", .{});
        try tui.present();

        switch (tui.waitEvent(-1)) {
            .key => |ke| if (ke.ch == 'q') running = false,
            else => {},
        }
    }

See examples/hello.zig and examples/demo.zig.


API REFERENCE
-------------

Generate locally with:

    doxygen Doxyfile
    # output: docs/html/index.html


BUILD TARGETS
-------------

  zig build                build everything
  zig build run-hello-c    run C example
  zig build run-hello-zig  run Zig example
  zig build run-demo       run C feature demo
  zig build run-demo-zig   run Zig feature demo


DEV ENVIRONMENT (NixOS)
------------------------

  nix develop   # or: direnv allow (requires .envrc with "use flake")

Provides: zig, zls, gcc, gdb, valgrind, bear, clang-tools.


